ance expansion. Throughout the book, he catalogs how surveillance generates information, the control of which creates and facilitates power, and potentially fuels state domination. The antidote, he argues, is a robust information law and policy that puts the power to monitor and regulate the police squarely in the hands of citizens.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aPolicezNorthwest, Pacificy21st century. 0aPrivacy, Right of. 0aSocial control. 0aVideo surveillancexSocial aspectszNorthwest, Pacificy21st century. 0aWearable video devices in police workzNorthwest, Pacificy21st century. 7aLAW / Media & the Law.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2021 Englishz978311075409408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2021z9783110753868oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520382923zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520382923423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520382923/original  a978-3-11-073915-2  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075409-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Law 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGCb2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021